I have attached the video that demos the current implementation of transactions list being scrolled and populated.

@benjthayer Previously the list was reset on new transactions received. Now items are added and moved around on new transactions fetched. Because new transactions might be added somewhere in between of already fetched ones both outside or inside of the visible area of the list view, we might want to show some animation for insertion for new transactions and displacing the existing ones. I have added some easy animation that just animates y position in all the cases, while trying to preserve the currently last visible transaction within the visible area. I'd appreciate your opinion on this. Would you prefer some other animation or maybe other behavior of the list view?
